From: Claw <claw@openclaw>
Date: Wed, 8 Apr 2026
Subject: [PATCH] Implement PJRT_Executable_DeserializeAndLoad for persistent compilation cache

Implements the previously-stubbed `PJRT_Executable_DeserializeAndLoad` API,
enabling the XLA persistent compilation cache (`xr.initialize_cache()`).

Background:
  Serialization (write side) was already implemented and working via
  `PJRT_Executable_Serialize` / `SerializedExecutableInstance` using the
  TTSERv00 binary format.  Deserialization (read side) was a stub returning
  kUnimplemented, so every process restart triggered a full recompile (93 min
  for Mochi 10B at 480×480/17f).

This patch:
  1. Adds `SerializedExecutableInstance::deserialize()` – a pure-C++ parser
     for the TTSERv00 header that extracts TTIR, TTNN, and flatbuffer sections.
  2. Adds `internal::onDeserializeAndLoad` in `client_instance.cc` which:
       a. Parses the TTSERv00 payload via `deserialize()`.
       b. Loads the pre-compiled flatbuffer binary from memory.
       c. Queries input/output counts, shapes, and data types directly from the
          `tt::runtime::Binary` API (getNumProgramInputs/Outputs, getProgramOutputs,
          getProgramMeshShape).
       d. Constructs default Identity (replicated) MeshSharding objects for
          each input/output — correct for non-SPMD models and for SPMD models
          where the XLA-visible I/O tensors are replicated across chips.
       e. Creates a `FlatbufferExecutableImage` and wraps it in a
          `FlatbufferLoadedExecutableInstance`, skipping all tt-mlir compilation.
  3. Removes `_STUB(PJRT_Executable_DeserializeAndLoad)` from `stubs.inc` and
     binds the real handler in `ClientInstance::bindApi`.

Expected performance impact:
  | Scenario               | Before (no cache)  | After (cache hit) |
  |------------------------|--------------------|-------------------|
  | 256×256/9f (4-chip)    | ~3.4 min           | ~0 s              |
  | 480×480/17f (Mochi)    | ~93 min            | ~0 s              |
  | 480×832/17f            | ~278 min           | ~0 s              |

Usage:
  import torch_xla as xr
  xr.initialize_cache("/tmp/tt_xla_cache")
  # First run: compiles + saves to disk.
  # Subsequent runs: loads from disk, skips compilation.

Limitations:
  - For SPMD models where XLA-visible inputs/outputs are themselves sharded
    (non-Identity shardings), the sharding information is not reconstructed
    from the serialized payload.  In practice, for torch_xla tensor-parallel
    models (Mochi, Wan2.1) the XLA-visible I/O tensors are replicated, so
    this limitation does not affect correctness.
  - `optimized_mlir_code` and `original_mlir_code` are not stored in the
    TTSERv00 format; they are set to empty strings in the deserialized image.
  - `compile_options` are reconstructed with `backend=TTNNFlatbuffer` defaults.

TODO:
  - Extend the TTSERv00 format (v01) to store sharding metadata so that
    non-trivial SPMD I/O shardings can be reconstructed without MLIR reparsing.
  - Tracked upstream: https://github.com/tenstorrent/tt-xla/issues/498

